text.__SUMMARY__: Chilorhinophis carpenteri, or the Liwale two-headed snake, is a species of venomous snakes in the family Atractaspididae.
text.Geographic range: C. carpenteri is endemic to Africa and is found in Mozambique and southeastern Tanzania.
text.Taxonomy: C. carpenteri was originally named Parkerophis carpenteri. Some herpetologists, including Battersby, consider C. carpenteri to be a synonym of C. butleri.
text.Etymology:
The specific name, carpenteri, honors the type specimen's collector, British physician and entomologist Geoffrey Douglas Hale Carpenter.
